statements: SELECT * FROM tracking_model_versioning WHERE model_version = 1;
SELECT experiment_id, model_version FROM tracking_model_versioning WHERE experiment_id = 100;
SELECT experiment_result FROM tracking_model_versioning WHERE model_version > 3;
SELECT experiment_id, model_version, experiment_result FROM tracking_model_versioning WHERE model_version = 2;
SELECT * FROM tracking_model_versioning WHERE experiment_id = 50;
SELECT * FROM tracking_model_versioning WHERE model_version > 5 ORDER BY experiment_id DESC;
SELECT experiment_id, COUNT(*) AS num_versions FROM tracking_model_versioning GROUP BY experiment_id HAVING COUNT(*) > 3;
SELECT experiment_id, model_version, jsonb_pretty(experiment_result) AS pretty_result FROM tracking_model_versioning WHERE model_version IN (3, 7, 9);
SELECT DISTINCT model_version FROM tracking_model_versioning ORDER BY model_version ASC LIMIT 2;

SELECT experiment_id, model_version, jsonb_extract_path_text(experiment_result, 'accuracy') AS accuracy FROM tracking_model_versioning WHERE model_version BETWEEN 4 AND 8 ORDER BY accuracy DESC, experiment_id ASC;
SELECT * FROM version_tracking;
SELECT model_name, model_version FROM version_tracking ORDER BY version_id DESC;

SELECT model_name, status FROM version_tracking ORDER BY version_id ASC;
SELECT * FROM version_tracking;
SELECT model_name, model_version FROM version_tracking WHERE status = 'active';

SELECT model_name, model_version, status FROM version_tracking WHERE model_version LIKE '%.1' AND status = 'active';
SELECT experiment_id, experiment_date, result FROM experiment_results WHERE result IS NOT NULL ORDER BY experiment_date ASC;

SELECT model_name, created_at FROM model_versions ORDER BY created_at DESC;

SELECT * FROM ModelVersions;
SELECT model_name, version_number, updated_at FROM ModelVersions ORDER BY version_number DESC;
SELECT id, experiment_name, experiment_type FROM Experiments WHERE started_at > '2022-01-01';

SELECT model_name, result, experiment_date FROM ModelVersions JOIN ModelVersionExperiments ON ModelVersions.id = ModelVersionExperiments.model_version_id JOIN ExperimentResults ON ModelVersionExperiments.experiment_id = ExperimentResults.id;
SELECT experiment_name, started_at, ended_at FROM Experiments WHERE ended_at IS NOT NULL AND experiment_type = 'A/B Test' ORDER BY started_at DESC;
